  ${
    $d k j n $.
    $( The sum of the reciprocals of the triangle numbers converge to two.
       (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 23-Apr-2014.) $)
    trirecip $p |- sum_ k e. ( ZZ>= ` 1 ) ( 2 / ( k x. ( k + 1 ) ) ) = 2 $=
      ( vn vj c1 c2 cv caddc co cmul cdiv csu wcel cc cc0 wne wceq syl11anc 2cn
      cli 1z cuz cfv cmpt cn elnnuz nncn peano2nn syl mulcl sylbir nnne0 mulne0
      syl22anc divrec mp3an1 id opreq1 opreq12d opreq2d eqid oprex fvmpt eqtr4d
      weq sumeq2i cz wral cop cseqz wbr reccl eqeltrd rgen trireciplem elisseti
      wex breq2 cla4ev ax-mp fvex mptex isummulc1 mp4an isumclim opreq2i eqtr3i
      mp2an mulid1i 3eqtri ) DUAUBZEAFZWKDGHZIHZJHZAKWJEWKBWJDBFZWODGHZIHZJHZUC
